  "text": "The full Deployment creation flow spans three layers:\n\n**Layer 1 \u2013 Client library (client-go):** The `deployments` struct in `kubernetes/typed/apps/v1/deployment.go` embeds `gentype.ClientWithListAndApply`. The actual `Create()` method is defined generically in `gentype/type.go` (`Client[T].Create`), which builds a POST request via `c.client.Post().Resource(...).Body(obj).Do(ctx)`. `Request.Do()` in `rest/request.go` calls `Request.request()` which executes the HTTP POST to the API server.\n\n**Layer 2 \u2013 API server (kubernetes/kubernetes):** The HTTP handler `createHandler` in `endpoints/handlers/create.go` receives the request, deserializes the body, runs admission controllers, then calls `r.Create()` which routes to `Store.Create()` in `registry/generic/registry/store.go`. This calls `rest.BeforeCreate()` which invokes `deploymentStrategy.Validate()` (in `pkg/registry/apps/deployment/strategy.go`), which delegates to `ValidateDeployment()` (in `pkg/apis/apps/validation/validation.go`). After validation, `Store.create()` calls `e.Storage.Create()` which invokes `store.Create()` in `staging/.../storage/etcd3/store.go`. This encodes the object, transforms it for storage, and calls `s.client.Kubernetes.OptimisticPut()` \u2013 a compare-and-swap transaction on the etcd client.\n\n**Layer 3 \u2013 etcd storage:** `OptimisticPut` (in `vendor/go.etcd.io/etcd/client/v3/kubernetes/client.go`) issues a Txn (compare ModRevision=0, then Put). On the etcd server side, `kvServer.Txn()` in `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/key.go` receives the gRPC call, which calls `EtcdServer.Txn()` in `v3_server.go`. For write txns this goes through Raft consensus via `raftRequest()`. Once committed, `applierV3backend.Put()` in `apply.go` handles the put operation, calling `storeTxnWrite.Put()` \u2192 `storeTxnWrite.put()` in `server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go`, which marshals the key-value pair and writes it to BoltDB via `tw.tx.UnsafeSeqPut()`.",
